-- Biocon, Essar Oil, Reliance, Sesa Goa, Tata Motors: India Equity Preview
-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r   a n d   R a j h k u m a r   K   S h a a w
-- 2010-10-19T02:51:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/biocon-essar-oil-reliance-sesa-goa-tata-motors-india-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in India  trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the  last close .  The Bombay Stock Exchange Sensitive Index, or  Sensex , rose
43.84, or 0.2 percent, to 20,168.89. The S&P CNX  Nifty  Index on
the National Stock Exchange advanced 0.2 percent to 6,075.95.
The  BSE 200 Index  increased 0.1 percent to 2,561.72.  SGX S&P CNX
Nifty Index futures  for October delivery climbed 0.3 percent to
6,149 as of 10:37 a.m. in Singapore.  Steelmakers:  JSW Steel Ltd.  (JSTL IN) and  Tata Steel Ltd. 
(TATA IN): The companies were rated “buy” in new coverage at
BNP Paribas, which said Indian steelmakers are likely to improve
their profitability, according to a report by  Alok Rawat  and
 Karan Gupta  that gave a share-price estimate of 1,662 rupees for
JSW Steel and a forecast of 773 rupees for Tata Steel’s stock.
They initiated coverage of  Steel Authority of India Ltd.  with a
“hold” recommendation and a price estimate of 210 rupees.  JSW Steel gained 0.3 percent to 1,318.8 rupees. Tata Steel
increased 1.6 percent to 646.05 rupees. Steel Authority dropped
0.4 percent to 219.3 rupees.  Adani Enterprises Ltd.  (ADE IN): India’s biggest coal
importer said it’s committed to a A$6.9 billion ($6.8 billion)
coal project in Queensland state. The stock fell 1.1 percent to
679.3 rupees.  Bharat Forge Ltd.  (BHFC IN): The maker of automotive parts
is evaluating coal mines in Mozambique, Indonesia and South
Africa that it may develop for its own use, the Business Line
newspaper reported, citing unidentified people. The company
plans to build 10,000 megawatts of power generating capacity in
the 10 years, the newspaper reported. The stock fell 1 percent
to 367.95 rupees.  Biocon Ltd.  (BIOS IN): Pfizer Inc., the world’s biggest
drugmaker, agreed to pay $200 million in upfront payments to
Biocon for rights to four insulin products to expand its
diabetes offerings in emerging markets. Biocon can get
additional milestone payments of as much as $150 million and
will receive payments linked to product sales by New York-based
Pfizer, the companies said in a statement. The biotechnology
company gained 0.8 percent to 403.10 rupees.  Indian Oil Corp Ltd.  (IOCL IN): The nation’s second-biggest
refiner was raised to “neutral” from “sell” by  Prakash Joshi , an analyst at UBS AG, with a price estimate of 430
rupees. The stock rose 1 percent to 406 rupees.  Reliance Industries Ltd . (RIL IN) and  Essar Oil Ltd.  (ESOIL
IN): India’s biggest non-state energy companies plan to bid in a
government auction of oil and gas blocks as the country seeks to
ramp up domestic production and cut imports. Reliance climbed
0.7 percent to 1,047.45 rupees. Essar Oil added 2.3 percent to
142.70 rupees.  Sesa Goa Ltd.  (SESA IN): India’s biggest iron-ore
exporter’s second-quarter profit more than doubled to 3.85
billion rupees in the three months ended Sept. 30., according to
its statement. The stock fell 0.5 percent to 372.4 rupees.  Tata Motors Ltd.  (TTMT IN): Citigroup Global Markets
Mauritius Pvt. sold 1.32 million Tata Motors’ ‘A’ shares with
differential voting rights to Broad Peak Mauritius Pvt. in a
bulk deal, according to data on the website of the National
Stock Exchange. The stock climbed 1.1 percent to 1,168.95
rupees.  To contact the reporters on this story:
